.Dd July 3, 2026
.Dt SOLIX-CLI 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm solix-cli
.Nd Anker Solix command-line interface
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl \-email Ar email
.Op Fl \-password Ar password
.Op Fl \-country Ar code
.Ar command
.Op Ar options
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
controls an Anker Solix 3 solar battery system via the Anker cloud API.
Credentials are read from environment variables or a
.Pa .env
file in the current directory.
All read commands accept
.Fl \-json
to emit raw JSON instead of formatted output.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm status
Show live power flow: PV input, battery state of charge, output power,
grid import, home load, and today's solar production in kWh.
.It Cm devices
List all registered devices with type, online status, battery SOC,
PV input, and output power.
.It Cm energy Op Fl \-days Ar n
Show daily energy totals for the past
.Ar n
days (default: 7).
Columns: solar production, battery charge, battery discharge,
grid-to-home, and home usage, all in kWh.
.It Cm config
Show current device configuration: operating mode, AI EMS state,
home load setting, backup reserve, and SOC cutoff thresholds.
.It Cm set-output Ar watts
Set the home load output power in watts.
.It Cm set-soc Op Fl \-min Ar pct Op Fl \-max Ar pct
Set battery SOC limits.
.Fl \-min
sets the discharge cutoff percentage;
.Fl \-max
sets the charge cutoff percentage.
At least one option is required.
.It Cm set-export Op Fl \-on | Fl \-off Op Fl \-limit Ar watts
Enable or disable grid export and optionally set a watt cap.
At least one option is required.
Note: may not be supported on all Solarbank 3 configurations.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev SOLIX_EMAIL
Anker account email address.
Also accepts
.Ev ANKERUSER
for compatibility with thomluther/anker-solix-api.
.It Ev SOLIX_PASSWORD
Anker account password.
Also accepts
.Ev ANKERPASSWORD .
.It Ev SOLIX_COUNTRY
Two-letter country code (default:
.Dq DE ) .
Also accepts
.Ev ANKERCOUNTRY .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa .env
Optional dotenv file loaded from the current directory.
Supports the same variable names as the environment.
See
.Pa .env.example
in the source tree.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Lk https://github.com/thomluther/anker-solix-api
.Sh CAVEATS
This tool uses an unofficial, reverse-engineered API.
Anker may change or revoke API access at any time without notice.
